Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Civil and Uncivil Societies
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01jmxsk
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 14 Jul 2012
The historian Niall Ferguson examines institutions outside the political, economic and legal realms, whose primary purpose is to preserve and transmit particular knowledge and values. In a lecture delivered at the Royal Society of Edinburgh, he asks if the modern state is quietly killing civil society in the Western world? And what can non-Western societies do to build a vibrant civil society? Producer: Jane Beresford. Show less